title: Exchange note - change code
text: If the client wants to change exchange note code, this is done in DdDAdmin under Adv. Configuration at the very bottom. The standard is GULDMØNTER (Goldcoins), but the client can choose a differen word that suits them better. Every letter equals a number, which shows the amount as a alphanumeric code at the bottom of their exchange note. G = 1 U = 2 L = 3 D = 4 M = 5 Ø = 6 N = 7 T = 8 E = 9 R = 0 Amount: 199,50 Code : gee,mr
description:
If the client wants to change exchange note code, this is done in DdDAdmin under Adv. Configuration at the very bottom. 

  

 

  

  

The standard is GULDMØNTER (Goldcoins), but the client can choose a differen word that suits them better. Every letter equals a number, which shows the amount as a alphanumeric code at the bottom of their exchange note. 

  

G = 1 

U = 2 

L = 3 

D = 4 

M = 5 

Ø = 6 

N = 7 

T = 8 

E = 9 

R = 0 

  

Amount: 199,50 

Code : gee,mr

title: Exchange note - changing date per sale
text: If the customer wants to be able to change the date on the exchange note for every sale, they need to change it from 1 to 2. 1. Log into POS and click Screen with Wrench button 2. Choose Store and Machine and change this machine only 3. Scroll down to Adv. Configuration, find Change Note Type and change it to 2. 4. Scroll down to bottom of page and click Save, then Close. 5. Reload the POS Now, when they scan an item and click on Exchange Note, they get this image, where they can change the date for issuing. The usual number of days to make an exchange is 8 days.
description:
If the customer wants to be able to change the date on the exchange note for every sale, they need to change it from 1 to 2. 

  

  1. 1. Log into POS and click Screen with Wrench button  

 

  

  1. 2. Choose Store and Machine and change this machine only 

  

 

  

  1. 3. Scroll down to Adv. Configuration, find Change Note Type and change it to 2. 

  

 

  

  

  1. 4. Scroll down to bottom of page and click Save, then Close. 

  

 

  

  1. 5. Reload the POS 

  

Now, when they scan an item and click on Exchange Note, they get this image, where they can change the date for issuing. The usual number of days to make an exchange is 8 days.
